net.xqhs.util.logging

Class UnitConfigData

  • java.lang.Object
    • Config
      • net.xqhs.util.logging.UnitConfigData

  • public class UnitConfigData
extends Config
    This configures a Unit. All configuration relates to logging.

    The main feature of the configuration is the name. If there is no name and other conditions are met, no log is created. See the constructor of Unit.

    Author:
    Andrei Olaru

    • Field Detail

      • unitName

        java.lang.String unitName
        The name of the Unit. See Unit for details.

      • addClassName

        boolean addClassName
        if true, the name of the class will be present in the name of this log, also according to the other settings in this group.

      • classNamePostfix

        boolean classNamePostfix
        If true, the name of the class will be concatenated after the name of the unit.

        If false, the name of the class will be concatenated before the name of the unit.

      • classNameLong

        boolean classNameLong
        If true, the complete name of the class will be used (including the package). Otherwise, only the name obtained by Class.getSimpleName() is used.

      • ensureNew

        boolean ensureNew
        If true, then if another log exists with the same name, an error will be produced. If false and another log with the same name exists, that log will be used.

      • level

        Log.Level level

      • display

        Logging.DisplayEntity display

      • reporter

        Logging.ReportingEntity reporter

      • loggerWrapperType

        Log.LoggerType loggerWrapperType

      • linkData

        UnitConfigData.UnitLinkData linkData

      • unitLink

        protected Unit unitLink
        Reference to the configured Unit (if applicable), for cases of communication to the Unit after instantiation.
